{"key":"post-7050165","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7050165</id>\n<content>It's not necessary to pH balance a substrate.  Casing layers are a different story, but the pH of coir is in the 5.5 to 6 range, which is just fine for a substrate.  Add between 5% to 10% gypsum to the coir as a nutrient boost, to provide calcium and supfur, which coir is deficient in.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>7049632</prev>\n<first>7049306</first>\n<last>7050165</last>\n<when>1181947090</when>\n<utime>06/16/07 01:38 AM</utime>\n</post>"}